    <note>Huang(2) Zhongyuan [11121] When the Song fell he changed his mingzi to Yuan and his zi to Tiansou. He was a teacher in the community in Yuan (jiaoshou yu xiang). Biographical sources cited in CBD have him as a 1266 jinshi, but Fujian TZ, 150.35a has him as a jinshi in 1271 (I use this date since no jinshi sitting in 1266). Huang Zhongyuan, WJ, 4.39b-44a. He married Ding(1) Nanyi's [11097] daughter at the age of 30. At the age of 50, in 1281, he took his younger brother of the same mother (Zhonghui's [11479] son, Zicai [11480]) as heir. His mother and her sister (both successive wives of father) were daughters of Song(2) Kegang [11478] (sororate). CBD, 4, 2893.</note>
